# Copy to .env.local (never commit secrets). See ../docs/vercel-environment.md for Vercel dashboard steps.
#
# --- Platform security (Cursor, Vercel, GitHub) — NOT controlled by this repo ---
# - Turn on 2FA for GitHub, Vercel, and Cursor; use app passwords or SSO where offered.
# - Never commit API keys; keep them only in Vercel/CI env or local .env.local (gitignored).
# - Restrict Vercel/GitHub repo access; rotate keys if a machine is lost.
# - Optional: set OPERATOR_APPROVAL_CODE below so only you (or anyone who knows the code)
#   can use Ask Rabbi (OpenAI) and developer session on this deployment.

# --- Optional owner approval (server-only) ---
# If set (≥ 32 random characters), users must POST /api/operator/unlock once per browser
# with this code; the app stores a signed HttpOnly cookie (8h), not the code in JS.
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
# OPERATOR_APPROVAL_CODE=

# --- Clerk (auth) — https://dashboard.clerk.com ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
# Optional explicit URLs (defaults work for local /sign-in and /sign-up):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up

# --- Site (client + metadata) ---
# Canonical URL for Open Graph / metadataBase (production), e.g. https://your-app.vercel.app
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# --- Sentry (optional) ---
# Client + server error reporting. Create a Next.js project at https://sentry.io
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
# Server-only override (defaults to NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN if unset):
# SENTRY_DSN=
# Source maps in CI/Vercel (optional): SENTRY_ORG, SENTRY_PROJECT, SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN

# --- Ask Rabbi — POST /api/rabbi (server only; never expose to the client) ---
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_RABBI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# Optional: disable LightRAG (local subprocess + remote retrieve; “Context unavailable” in prompt)
# RABBI_USE_LIGHTRAG=0
# Remote retrieval (Railway FastAPI): base URL only, no trailing path — e.g. https://lightrag-api.up.railway.app
# RABBI_LIGHTRAG_RETRIEVE_URL=
# Shared secret; must match LIGHTRAG_RETRIEVE_SECRET on the Python service
# RABBI_LIGHTRAG_RETRIEVE_SECRET=
# Monorepo root if `next dev` cwd is not `web/` (usually unnecessary)
# RABBI_REPO_ROOT=
# Windows: PYTHON_EXE=py

# --- Developer mode (owner — unlocks all course gates in-browser) ---
# Comma-separated list of Clerk user IDs allowed to obtain a dev session (find in Clerk dashboard → Users → ID, e.g. user_2ab...).
# Keep private: anyone in this list can enable dev tools for their Clerk account.
# DEVELOPER_CLERK_USER_IDS=
# HMAC secret for the dev-session cookie. Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32  (must be ≥ 32 chars).
# DEVELOPER_SESSION_SECRET=

# --- GET/PUT/DELETE /api/progress (optional Learn backup in KV; see docs/cloud-progress.md) ---
# Link Vercel KV to the project; these are usually auto-filled by Vercel (do not commit values)
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# --- Navigation (client) ---
# If "true", hides the Developer link from the hamburger menu (production hardening).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_HIDE_DEVELOPER_NAV=

# --- POST /api/mcq-choices, /api/validate-hebrew-passage, /api/progress, GET /api/hebcal/snapshot ---
# Rate limits use the same Vercel KV when KV_REST_* are set. Without KV: skipped in development.
# Lexicon: npm run extract:corpus-d

# --- POST /api/mcq-choices ---
# No extra env. Lexicon is web/data/corpus-d.ts (committed).
